PrecisAmendments to the CANADIAN WHEAT BOARD REGULATIONS which establish higher initial payments for the BASE GRADES of WHEAT (from $110 to $135 per tonne), AMBER DURUM WHEAT (from $125 to $150), BARLEY (from $75 to $90), and DESIGNATED BARLEY (from $110 to $135) in the 1994-95 crop year, effective October 24, 1994.
